## Main Looping and Sampling

This area is the "retrieval hub" for all our global settings using Get/Set nodes. It also does all our sampling, color matching, extending and stitching videos together.

It outputs to a VFI to double the frames from 16 to 32, then finally combines all these into an output video file with Video Combine.

## Prompting

The **WanVideoLooper Prompts** node enables you to *Load*, *Save*, and *Name* profiles. 

It accepts multiple prompts, each per line. You can double line to create a break and it will move to the next textual prompt.

## LoRa Loading & Sequencing

This section loads LoRas onto the base models (from the "Loaders" group) and prepares them for sequencing.

* **PowerLoraLoaderV2 (ID 42, 44, 45):** Each of these nodes can load a LoRa (for both high and low models) and set its strength. You can chain them together to stack multiple LoRas. The workflow is setup to use minimal amount of LoRas to keep things simple, but you can add up to five using the sequencer.

* **WanVideoLoraSequencer (ID 43):** This is the key node for LoRa stacking. It takes up to 5 different model inputs (e.g., models with different LoRas or LoRa strengths) and sequences them.

* The `WanVideoLooper` (the main sampler) will use this sequence to change the LoRa's effect over the duration of the video.

The way the Power Lora Loader V2 (QQ) works is that if your high model naming has something like "name_High" and "name_Low" for the High/Low models (filenames) then when you load the High model it will show a green light next to it which means it detected the low model and automatically loads that too. If not, there's a naming conflict, such as no Low model or named oddly such as "HM" "LM".

## Loader Subgraph

This is the only subgraph in our workflow and it contains all the loaders. You can use whatever models you wish here, they are prefilled with some defaults that work for me.

## Workflow Controls

This workflow uses **Get/Set nodes** to pass settings, which keeps the graph clean. The main controls are in the "Settings" group to the right.

* **LoadImage (ID 39):** Load your single starting image here.
* **WanVideoAutoImgResize (ID 22):** This node automatically resizes your start image to the chosen resolution (e.g., "480p"). It then **Sets** the final `Width` and `Height` variables, which are used by the sampler.

* **Duration:** Sets the total video length in seconds.
* **Steps:** Number of sampling steps. 6-8 is good for this model.
* **Sigma Shift:** Adjusts the noise schedule. 8 is a good default for the Wan I2V model.
* **Seed:** Sets the seed for generation.

You can disable Sage Attention in the Bypasser if you don't need it.
